The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Briefs
                                                                                                                       7                                                                                                        
	London: A critic of the event since its inception, former England captain Nasser Hussain has once again lashed out at the Indian Premier League (IPL) and said the recent controversy surrounding the league has proved that no tournament was bigger than the game.    
	Hussain said the IPL has acquired the size of a monster, and criticised its suspended chairman and commissioner Lalit Modi for tying to become bigger than the game. The biggest lesson cricket can learn from the allegations swirling around the IPL is that no tournament should attempt to become bigger than the game itself, Hussain wrote in a newspaper column.        
	Calcutta: The England and Wales Cricket Board Wednesday confirmed that Surrey player Andre Nel has received an automatic suspension under its discipline code. Nel was reported by the umpires for a Level Two breach of the code (showing serious dissent at an umpires decision by word or action), for which he has received three penalty points.         
	Dubai: China were stripped of a bronze medal from the 2000 Sydney Olympics on Wednesday for fielding an underage female gymnast, with the womens team medal now going to the United States.         
	New Delhi: Indian boxers Shiva Thapa (54kg) and J Bhaskar (51kg) notched up contrasting wins to advance to the pre-quarter finals of the World Youth Championships in Baku, Azerbaijan Wednesday.           
	New Delhi: A 21-member Indian table tennis team has reached Zhengding, for a 25-day training stint to prepare for the forthcoming World Championships in Moscow from May 23-30.           
	London: Manchester City have lined up Hungarian international Marton Fulop on loan from Premier League rivals Sunderland to resolve a goalkeeping crisis threatening their bid for a Champions League qualifying place.           
	n Buenos Aires: Former Argentina World Cup forward Ariel Ortega was a surprise inclusion on Tuesday in a squad named by coach Diego Maradona for a friendly against Haiti next week.         
	New Delhi: Top seeded pair of Rohan Bopanna and Aisam-ul-Haq Qureshi advanced to the doubles quarter finals of the ATP Tunis Open in Tunisia after a getting a walkover from Theirry Ascione and Arnaud Clement in the first round.         
	Calcutta: Shivika Burman moved into the second round of singles and doubles in the $10,000 ITF Womens Circuit in Antalya, Turkey. In singles, she beat Croatias Tea Fabar 3-6, 6-4, 6-3, according to information received here. Partnering Croatias Sonja Liasovska, she got the better of Koek (Netherlands) and Verhamme (Belgium) 7-6, 4-6, 11-9 in doubles.
